cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes an interactive learning framework for vision and language navigation, which involves natural language processing (NLP), computer vision (CV), and reinforcement learning (RL). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the agent's ability to navigate in a physical environment, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper utilizes image and language data, which is relevant to cs.CV. Finally, the paper proposes a continual learning strategy, which involves updating the agent's knowledge over time, making cs.LG a possible sub-category.
